diff --git a/dwm.1 b/dwm.1
index ddc8321..8bccbc0 100644
--- a/dwm.1
+++ b/dwm.1
@@ -35,6 +35,13 @@ dwm draws a small border around windows to indicate the focus state.
 .B \-v
 prints version information to stderr, then exits.
 .SH USAGE
+.P
+.B Mod
+in the following commands refer to
+.BR Mod4 ,
+or the
+.B SUPER/Windows
+key.
 .SS Status bar
 .TP
 .B X root window name
@@ -46,115 +53,127 @@ command.
 click on a tag label to display all windows with that tag, click on the layout
 label toggles between tiled and floating layout.
 .TP
+.B Button2
+click on the window title to cycle the focused window between master and
+stacking area.
+.TP
 .B Button3
 click on a tag label adds/removes all windows with that tag to/from the view.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Button1
+.B Mod\-Button1
 click on a tag label applies that tag to the focused window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Button3
+.B Mod\-Button3
 click on a tag label adds/removes that tag to/from the focused window.
 .SS Keyboard commands
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-Return
-Start
-.BR st(1).
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-p
-Spawn
-.BR dmenu(1)
-for launching other programs.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-,
+.B Mod\-,
 Focus previous screen, if any.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-.
+.B Mod\-.
 Focus next screen, if any.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-,
+.B Mod\-Shift\-,
 Send focused window to previous screen, if any.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-.
+.B Mod\-Shift\-.
 Send focused window to next screen, if any.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-b
-Toggles bar on and off.
+.B Mod\-F11
+Toggles the default panel on or off.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-t
+.B Mod\-Shift\-t
 Sets tiled layout.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-f
+.B Mod\-Shift\-f
 Sets floating layout.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-m
+.B Mod\-Shift\-m
 Sets monocle layout.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-space
+.B Mod\-space
 Toggles between current and previous layout.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-j
+.B Mod\-j
 Focus next window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-k
+.B Mod\-k
 Focus previous window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-i
+.B Mod\-=
 Increase number of windows in master area.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-d
+.B Mod\--
 Decrease number of windows in master area.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-l
+.B Mod\-l
 Increase master area size.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-h
+.B Mod\-h
 Decrease master area size.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Return
+.B Mod\-Shift\-l
+Decrease height of the focused window with respect to other windows sharing the
+master/stacking area.
+.TP
+.B Mod\-Shift\-h
+Increase height of the focused window with respect to other windows sharing the
+master/stacking area.
+.TP
+.B Mod\-Shift\-o
+Reset all windows in the master/stacking area to have equal heights.
+.TP
+.B Mod\-Return
 Zooms/cycles focused window to/from master area (tiled layouts only).
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-c
+.B Mod\-q
 Close focused window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-space
+.B Mod\-Shift\-space
 Toggle focused window between tiled and floating state.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Tab
+.B Mod\-Tab
 Toggles to the previously selected tags.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-[1..n]
+.B Mod\-Shift\-[1..n]
 Apply nth tag to focused window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-0
+.B Mod\-Shift\-0
 Apply all tags to focused window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Control\-Shift\-[1..n]
+.B Mod\-Control\-Shift\-[1..n]
 Add/remove nth tag to/from focused window.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-[1..n]
+.B Mod\-[1..n]
 View all windows with nth tag.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-0
+.B Mod\-0
 View all windows with any tag.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Control\-[1..n]
+.B Mod\-Control\-[1..n]
 Add/remove all windows with nth tag to/from the view.
-.TP
-.B Mod1\-Shift\-q
-Quit dwm.
 .SS Mouse commands
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Button1
+.B Mod\-Button1
 Move focused window while dragging. Tiled windows will be toggled to the floating state.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Button2
+.B Mod\-Button2
 Toggles focused window between floating and tiled state.
 .TP
-.B Mod1\-Button3
+.B Mod\-Button3
 Resize focused window while dragging. Tiled windows will be toggled to the floating state.
 .SH CUSTOMIZATION
 dwm is customized by creating a custom config.h and (re)compiling the source
 code. This keeps it fast, secure and simple.
+.P
+Some options can be alternatively customized through
+.B Xresources
+with
+.B dwm
+prefix. See the source code for which settings can be provided through this
+method.
 .SH SEE ALSO
 .BR dmenu (1),
 .BR st (1)
